The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 New York hotel checks into Tata fold

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Mumbai, June 27: Indian Hotels of the Tata group today announced that it has signed a 30-year contract to operate and manage The Pierre, a luxurious landmark hotel on New Yorks Fifth Avenue, for a lease amount of $5 million per annum. Taj Hotels Resorts and Palaces will take over the management of The Pierre.

 Taj will retain the current mix of hotel rooms and permanent resident spaces at The Pierre. Over the next few months, it will upgrade and renovate some portions of the hotel at a cost of $35 million.

 Tajs acquisition of The Pierre is in line with the companys strategy to establish a presence in key gateway cities of the world. 

 The Pierre has all the hallmarks of a great hotel ? rich heritage, splendid location and grand old-world architecture. We are delighted to mark our return to New York with this iconic hotel and we are committed to ensuring it continues to symbolise uncompromised luxury not only in this market but around the world as well. Our return to New York is a step towards establishing a global presence for the Taj brand, said Raymond Bickson, Indian Hotels MD and CEO. 




